title: AREA ROUNDUP: Three second-half goals power Red Jacket girls over H-AC
text: Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:32 PM By Messenger Post Posted Oct. 14, 2015 at 10:32 PM Canandaigua, N.Y. SHORTSVILLE — Sara VanAken scored three second-half goals to lead the Red Jacket girls soccer team to a 3-2 victory over H-AC (12-3) on Wednesday. The Wolves went into the half with a 2-0 lead, but the Indians were able to score three early second-half goals and hold on for the win. Olivia Spencer led Red Jacket (5-9) in net with 15 saves. H-AC’s Juliana Stoddard had two assists, while Danielle Geary and Sunniva Sheffield each scored a goal for the Wolves. Alexis Gardner, Sophie Busch and Rylee North each had an assist for Red Jacket. Abby O’Brien made 12 saves in goal for the Wolves. Red Jacket has won four of its last five games and will host South Seneca on Friday. In other high school girls soccer action on Wednesday: Dundee 3, Romulus 0 Tayler Morrison recorded a hat trick for the Scotsmen, and Andi Wood made 13 saves to earn the shutout. Emma Voorhees made 18 saves for Romulus in net. South Seneca 7, Honeoye 3 Jenna McDonald scored four goals for the Falcons, and Emily Dey and MacKenzie Kenyon each had a goal and an assist. Mackenzie Rudolph made seven saves for the Bulldogs. South Seneca clinched its first league title with the win. Geneva 1, Midlakes 0 Sydney Mittiga scored off a pass from Nya Clark to lead the Panthers, and Sarah Bonsu recorded the shutout in net. Jen Maslyn made four saves in goal for Midlakes. Wayne 7, Pal-Mac 0 Adrianna VanCuyck had two goals and two assists to lead the Eagles over the Red Raiders. Bailey Jenkins earned the shutout with seven saves in net. Newark 3, Penn Yan 0 Makalah Crawford helped the Reds shut out the Mustangs with one save in goal. Mckenna Pettit scored two goals and had an assist for Newark. Bloomfield 2, Naples 1 Kimberly Tiffany scored the game winner 31 minutes into the second half. Mika Hobart scored the lone goal of the game for Naples. TUESDAY BOYS SOCCER H-AC 3, Marcus Whitman 0 Xin Yao scored the first two goals and Manny Hanuch scored the third for Harley-Allendale Columbia (10-2, 11-4). Tim Cornish made six saves for Marcus Whitman (1-10, 2-13). By Messenger Post
